<node TEXT="Home Test Cases" POSITION="left" FOLDED="true">
<node TEXT="Positive Functional" POSITION="left" FOLDED="true">
<node TEXT="1. Clicking the Home link in the header navigates the user to the homepage." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="2. The Home link is visible and accessible from all pages of the website." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="3. The Home link is highlighted when the user is on the homepage." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="4. The Home link loads the homepage content without errors." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="5. The Home link is accessible via keyboard navigation (Tab key)." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="6. The Home link has an appropriate aria-label for screen readers." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="7. The Home link opens the homepage in the same browser tab." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="8. The Home link is present in the mobile navigation menu." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="9. The Home link is styled consistently with other navigation links." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="10. The Home link is clickable and responds to user interaction." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
</node>
<node TEXT="Negative Functional" POSITION="left" FOLDED="true">
<node TEXT="1. Clicking the Home link while already on the homepage does not reload the page unnecessarily." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="2. Removing the Home link from the DOM prevents navigation to the homepage." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="3. Disabling the Home link makes it unclickable and does not navigate." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="4. Entering an invalid URL for the Home link results in a 404 error." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="5. The Home link does not navigate to an external website." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="6. The Home link does not trigger any JavaScript errors when clicked." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="7. The Home link does not open multiple tabs when clicked repeatedly." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="8. The Home link does not overlap with other navigation elements." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="9. The Home link does not disappear when resizing the browser window." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
<node TEXT="10. The Home link does not trigger navigation if the user right-clicks and selects 'Open in new tab' and the link is set to open in the same tab." FOLDED="true" POSITION="left" />
</node>
<node TEXT="Non-Functional" POSITION="left" FOLDED="true">
